uitae praestitit melius. · PLINY, Nat. Hist. vii 167.

1 Paulinus.

This dialogue (which, like the other so-called dia- logues² of Seneca, is not really a dialogue but a treatise) is nominally addressed to one Paulinus But, though he is mentioned in the first line, and Chapters 18 and 19 contain a personal appeal to him by name, yet the treatise as a whole is not addressed ‘co any individual but to the reading public of Rome and the Empire. Α
